commentTextItems.html: edged in the air, Twose may get a catch at the long on, but no, the terrific fans, a credit to the human race, storm onto the field, Twose aborts going for the catch and instead seeks out some protection

commentPostTextItems.html: and as expected Pakistan qualify for the 1999 World Cup final, a commanding performance. New Zealand get to hang around for the encore 4-Test match series
a huge crowd has gathered in front of the pavilion. Stay tuned and we'll have a summary of the presentations being fully drowned out by the crowd noise
Ravi Shastri is the MC, and don't the crowd just love him

Fleming gets a healthy boo as well. "we had a reasonable competitive total... Shoaib very quick... we thought we may have got them with the lack of pace (!).... we exceeded expectation for a lot of people [in terms of the tournament, not the match]"
Wasim: "reaching the final of the world cup is a great achievemnt...", he doesn't care who he plays in the final
Richie Benaud chooses Shoaib as the Man of the Match, not for his economy I assume. A pretty surprising choice over Saeed Anwar.
and then there were 3. Tomorrow is the second semi final, Australia v South Africa from Birmingham. As usual, 0945 GMT. Good night.

commentTextItems.html: slogged over the bowler's head, 2 to win
another ripper of a ball, zips past the outside edge yet again, Allott may not get a chance to bowl another over

commentTextItems.html: defending down the wicket, back to the bowler
moving away from the batsman and to the keeper
and again past the outside edge, Allott finally pulling his finger out

commentPostTextItems.html: people running onto the pitch for some unknown reason
fans jumping over the fence, and squatting on the rope, security doesn't appear to give two hoots about it
a big delay it will be, my crowd's overfloweth!
I suspect there might be a pitch invasion at the conclusion of this match. Just call it a hunch.
game won't be restarting until all the crowd are packed back into their tin
finally, play is about to continue after a 9 minute delay. Most of the crowd simply stared blankly and ignore the request to get back into the stands

commentTextItems.html: zipping it past the outside the edge, Ijaz dabbing some defence at it
Allott brought back, and not a moment too soon
and there's another few runs, we're nearly there
